Indexr is currently in MVP crunch mode for YC Summer 2026.

Current product scope:
- Chain: Arbitrum only
- Launch funds: INDXR-BAE and INDXR-10 only
- Product: simple, rules-based, non-custodial crypto index investing
- Priority: guarded beta with real deposits, clear safety controls, and simple UX

In scope:
- contract deployment
- frontend wiring
- deposit / redeem flows
- transaction history
- dashboard correctness
- deterministic, simple portfolio behavior
- admin controls, caps, pause controls
- test coverage for money-moving flows

Out of scope for now:
- AI Signals Engine
- Open Banking / VRP
- smart wallet abstraction
- locker-per-user vault architecture
- multi-chain support
- additional funds beyond INDXR-BAE and INDXR-10
- heavy infra / Kubernetes / microservices
- speculative future products

Engineering principles:
- no fake enterprise complexity
- prefer the smallest correct implementation
- always distinguish real functionality from mocks/placeholders
- all money-moving code must be tested before merge
- optimize for speed, safety, clarity, and one-person operability
